cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with feature level fusion of face and palmprint biometrics using scale invariant feature points (SIFT) and isomorphic graph. This falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses an improved K-medoids clustering algorithm and iterative relaxation algorithm for searching the most probable pair of graphs. This involves machine learning techniques and hence falls under this category. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the fusion of face and palmprint biometrics, which are both multimedia data types. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Biometric systems are often used for security purposes and the paper deals with improving the accuracy of such systems. Hence, it could fall under this category. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with feature level fusion of biometric data, which could be used for information retrieval purposes.
